<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-62] surefire xml report not wellformed on junit returning int</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-62</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Surefire XML reports are not well-formed, they contain unescaped &quot;&amp;lt;&quot; and &quot;&amp;gt;&quot; characters when JUnit reports a failed assertEquals(1,2) with int.&lt;br/&gt;
Putting attached SurefireXmlTest into your tests directory brings XML-results like the attached.&lt;br/&gt;
excerpt:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;failure type=&quot;junit.framework.AssertionFailedError&quot; message=&quot;expected:&amp;lt;1&amp;gt; but was:&amp;lt;2&amp;gt;&quot;&amp;gt;junit.framework.AssertionFailedError: expected:&amp;lt;1&amp;gt; but was:&amp;lt;2&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As you see, the element content is properly escaped, but not the content of attribute &quot;message&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Windows XP Pro, Java 1.5.0_06</environment>
